COPILOT PROMPT:

We are migrating a static magazine website (index.html + app.js) to GitHub Pages.
We need a backend API using Google Apps Script + Google Sheets.

IMPORTANT:
- Do NOT change the website layout.
- Images must not disappear: store image URLs in the sheet.
- Support image uploads to Google Drive (from Admin) and return a permanent public URL.

Create:
1) Google Sheets schema (tabs and columns)
2) Apps Script Web App endpoints

Sheets tabs:
- critics
  columns: id, createdAt, title, artist, score, statusTag, excerpt, body, coverImageUrl, author, isDemo, slug
- news
  columns: id, createdAt, label, headline, subtitle, author, date, heroImageUrl, opening, body, pullQuote, isDemo, slug
- interviews
  columns: id, createdAt, label, guestName, headline, subtitle, author, date, heroImageUrl, opening, body, pullQuote, isDemo, slug
- charts
  columns: id, createdAt, chartTitle, issueNumber, date, status, entriesJson, isDemo

API requirements:
- Web app must respond with JSON and include CORS headers.
- Use a simple admin token check: requests must include X-ADMIN-TOKEN header (or token field), reject otherwise.

Endpoints:
- POST /uploadImage
  payload: { fileName, mimeType, base64Data }
  behavior: save into a specific Drive folder (create if missing), set sharing to "anyone with link", return { ok:true, url }
- POST /publishCritic
- POST /publishNews
- POST /publishInterview
- POST /publishChart
  publishChart must reject if entries < 10 and store entries as JSON string in entriesJson
- POST /seedDemo (mode 1 or 3)
- POST /deleteDemo

Also include:
- GET /list?type=critics|news|interviews|charts (optional but helpful)

Deliver:
- Full Apps Script code (Code.gs) with doGet/doPost router
- Helper functions: requireToken, jsonResponse, parseBody, saveRow
- Instructions for deployment (publish as web app, access: anyone, set token in script properties)
